From d8be5fff80e3ad635e52d8b926547cffbce74c6e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Oliver Beard <olib141@outlook.com>
Date: Thu, 29 Jan 2026 14:16:20 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/4] frontend/greeter: Fix not waking on keys, and implement
 escape key like screen locker

Now the greeter handles key presses through an event filter, waking the prompt whenever a key is pressed.

The screen locker implementation relies upon an obscure behaviour of unblocking the ui timeout making it display, which was prematurely optimised out.

In order to accept all key input and since escape key needs to go to C++ anyway, we use an event filter object on the window and share it with QML so that it can wake or timeout as needed.

Like in the screen locker, we also clear the password when escape is pressed and the display turned off, as well as on suspend/hibernate.

Finally, we also set the cursorShape when the greeter is hidden.

Closes #43.
